    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <head>No. 124.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Washburne</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-10-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 9,
                                1871</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 335.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The following extract from a report made
                            by Minister Leon to the Congress of Ecuador, a copy of which accompanied
                            a dispatch of the 21st of August last, from our minister at Quito, is
                            transmitted for your information: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Our citizens in Paris having been exposed to the consequences of
                                    the horrible Franco-German war without any Ecuadorian diplomatic
                                    agent which could protect their persons and property, found in
                                    the minister plenipotentiary (the Hon. E. B. Washburne) of the
                                    United States of America aid and protection.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
